    %h2(id="#20110504")
      4th May 2011: New website!

    %p
      The Aeolus Community have launched the second version of our main website.

    %p
      Designed by Kyle Baker from the Red Hat User Experience (UX) Team, this
      one is visually appealing, has a
      %b much
      cleaner look, and is very easy to locate information in.

    %p
      Importantly, this website begins addressing the needs of business and
      non-technical Aeolus users.  A marked improvement over the developer only
      focus of the previous website.

    %p
      It is expected this will be a key piece for Aeolus growing into the
      worlds best cloud deployment software.

    %p
      %b UPDATE:
      Although we mentioned Kyle Baker's UX Design work for the new site,
      we unintentionally forgot to mention
      %a{ :href => "http://jimmac.musichall.cz/",
          :title => "Jakub Steiner's website" } Jakub Steiner's
      significant work.  Jakub created the new Aeolus logo, did the majority
      of the heavy lifting for the site's CSS, plus much more.  Due to his
      effort, the site works well in all major browsers, resizes and scales
      properly, loads quickly, and generally behaves as it should.  Thanks
      Jakub!

